verbose_text: XREF_BIBR Big data includes agronomic data (yield, soil properties, pesticide and fertilizer application rates, planting density, genotypes, etc), machine data (GPS and sensor derived information, yield monitors, etc), spatial and imaging data (GIS [geographic information system], satellite, and remote sensing imagery, near infrared reflectance, etc), and meteorological data (precipitation, temperature, atmospheric gas levels, etc) (XREF_TABLE).
